This IPhone 13 Pro has been phenomenal. The speed at which it operates is Incredible. If you are questioning this buy, don’t. It’s a wonderful deal. I’ve not had one issue thus far, and will most certainly update this review if I have one within the warranty period. I recommend getting a tempered glass screen and a good case—this phone is glass front and back.

I loved how new this phone looks and works. Everything works and the battery life was at 94% which is very good. I am very glad with this purchase and definitely recommend buying from them. Very skeptical before buying but now having the product it is definitely worth a buy if you are looking for a good phone

I'm rewriting my review because i bought this keyboard brand new and the shift button on this keyboard was very iffy to begin but i shrugged it off because it was at least working. But now it just plainly does not work. I have to get a new keyboard due to this

I've bought this keyboard twice now. It looks and feels great, and with both keyboards, keys start getting bound to each other for no reason. Last time, every time I hit my R key, the keyboard would enter ER. Now, when I hit the 1 key, it enters 12 every single time. I've popped off those caps a dozen times, tried compressed air to maybe move something around. Reinstalled drivers, updates, restarted, windows updates, changes usb ports, nothing works. Great for aesthetic purchases. Terrible for reliability.

A backlit keyboard that doesn't sound like a bucket of marbles when you type. A huge plus. Space bar squeeked when I got it - had to pull that off and grease it. Also, it took me a bit to notice it, but the Shift characters are UNDER the main characters. What are they thinking - that's so weird.

The shift function is usually signified with an UP arrow. When you look at the ? key, the ? should be on top of the /. The $ should be above the 4. This keyboard has the symbols reversed! bugs the hell out of me, but it works.

So technically this is a bit of a downgrade from my old Razor Huntsman Elite. However, I'm a lap-typer as in I primarily keep my keyboard in my lap when I type and that Huntsman was heavy and bigger than I needed or wanted. Picked this up as a lighter, smaller alternative and I love it! The lighting, while not as precise, is still very nice as I like to customize certain keys to be lit up in certain colors. There is significant bleed when you have two certain competing colors programmed to be right next to eachother but it doesn't bother me too much. Definitely a 5 star keyboard for the price!
I used a mechanical keyboard for a year and it's just not for me. So I went back to this Keyboard and man am I blown away. The feel in a Razer keyboard is amazing, even in this cheap model.

I bought this keyboard because the keyboard that came with my pc tower stopped working. I knew I wanted my next keyboard to be geared more towards gaming. My tower also lights up, so if the keyboard has lights too, that's even better. The Razer Cynosa V2 keys themselves have grooves like a skateboard vertical ramp. You can move left or right. It's smooth. In the Chroma customization, you can choose the colors and where you want them to light up. They have presets (numbers, letters, etc) so you can easily select the colors you want in the basic areas. I had a more detailed scheme in mind. The purple, light blue, and blue seem to blur into each other. Choosing a white color in between seems to help. As you can see there is a lot of fun lighting you can do with this keyboard..and it's comfortable for gaming.

I use this on a 2nd computer. I really do like it. Very much. But I gave it 4 stars simply because Razer, for some reason, has decided to not include independent macro keys. Lighting is fine, and someone in their infinite wisdom decided to light up the !@#$%^&*()_+ keys (unlike the Blackwidow keyboards), which is great! As usual for Razer, the software can sometimes be a pain, and if you have an older Razer product, you'll need to use 2 different versions of their software... That really makes no sense! Don't get me wrong... I'm really happy with my purchase, I just wish Razer would incorporate all of their products into a single software package, and bring back independent macro keys!

Great quality keyboard, but the synapse program is horrible. I didn't really care for all the extra features I just wanted a good quality keyboard. Keyboard is awesome, its hefty and the keys feel great. After the first few days of owning it I uninstalled the synapse program because it just causes constant problems with the lighting and sometimes even the keyboard itself. Often I'd have to completely restart my computer to get the lights to turn back on, ending processes and restarting synapse wouldn't work half the time. Soft to type slight click with bright LEDS works wit OpenRGB so you dont need Synaspe from Razer

It’s absolutely amazing. No sticking keys, completely customizable lighting, no weird steps to setting it up, two different levels of kickstands, 3 different ways to route the cable, absolutely no complaints.
